The fire , for still unknown reason, broke out at 9:44 p.m. on Friday inside a toy stock room on the third floor of the Metro Ayala department store, an eight-level building that formed part of the sprawling Ayala Center Cebu mall complex located at the Cebu Business Park.

Tadeo said they remained under Task Force Bravo, which means that the presence of all firefighting units from as far as Danao City in the north and Naga City in the south are still needed to assist the Cebu City Fire Department in battling the Metro Ayala fire .

UPDATE: At 2:05 a.m. today, firefighters have doused the ball of fire that crept out of the burning Metro Ayala department store past 9 p.m. on Saturday but FSSupt. Samuel Tadeo said they could not yet declare a fire out since the inside of the building continues to burn pic.twitter.com/mavs4xoSy5
